File: EFF leader Julius Malema is challenging the constitutionality of the Riotous Assemblies Act of 1956. PRETORIA - Economic Freedom Fighters leader Julius Malema is appearing in the North Gauteng High Court on Thursday. Malema is challenging the constitutionality of the Riotous Assemblies Act of 1956. He has been charged with violating the Act at least twice -- once in Newcastle in KwaZulu-Natal and again in Bloemfontein, where he urged supporters to invade vacant land. READ:Â SAHRC: Malema comments not hate speech Malema appeared in the Bloemfontein magistrate's court in June in relation to the matter. During that appearance, his legal team asked for the case in the North Gauteng High Court to be heard first. That trial has been put on hold pending the outcome of the constitutional challenge.